RACE.RACE_TEXT: BELMONT PARK RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 86. Maiden Special Weight Purse 60000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. (Non-starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred). (If the S tewards consider it inadvisable to run this race on the turf course, this race will be run at One Mile on the main track.) (Rail at 27 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHANGEWILLDOYAGOOD sat reserved during the opening stages, angled out into the four path during the first half of the run around the bend, tipped one wider shortly afterwards, got set down spinning into the stretch, drifted out while put to a strong left handed stick, closed in more readily once past the eighth pole, outfinished a pair of rivals in the final seventy yards to prove best. STENSON launched a three wide run to establish control, was sent over closer to the rail heading down the backstretch, got put to encouragement with none latched on entering the stretch, held out until the final seventy yards before relinquishing, then was vanned off after crossing the wire. FOREVER UTOPIA underwent a three wide journey and raced willingly to the end en route to securing the show. TALLADEGA swung four wide into the stretch and made steadily progress towards the front runners. MASSOLIMO got checked after striking the left side of the gate, quickly tucked along the rail, was already under a full drive cutting the corner into the stretch, mustered up a mild response. EASTCOAST LIGHTS took up the chase from the two path, lacked the needed response. STARAGO out sharply, was pulled away from any possible contact with another as the field was sent on its way, settled along the inside route quickly, appeared headstrong with the pilot having to steady the mount along until the five-sixteenths pole, was put to some hand urging being sent to the outside at the point, entered the stretch about three wide, made no impact. WARRIOR'S HERO out slightly at the start, saved ground to no avail. HUNTER GREY strung out four wide on both the chute and full turn, folded.

ENTRY.NAME: Warrior's Hero
ENTRY.OWNER: Engel, Charles F. and Ogden, Donald P.
ENTRY.COMMENT: out bit start, saved ground to no avail

ENTRY.NAME: Talladega
ENTRY.OWNER: Stonegate Racing Stables J and M Racing Stables and Hicks John P

ENTRY.NAME: Stenson
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w run to lead,near 2p turn,drive 1/4,caught final 70,vanned off

ENTRY.NAME: Starago
ENTRY.COMMENT: out sharp st,headstrong & steadied along,ins to 5/16,no factor

ENTRY.NAME: Massolimo
ENTRY.OWNER: Bond Tina Marie Sleeper Stables and Happy Racing Stables
ENTRY.COMMENT: hit gate, checked start, drive cutting corner, mildly

ENTRY.NAME: Forever Utopia
ENTRY.OWNER: That's Amore Stable, McMahon, M., Ragosta, G., Rabl, W. and Gardella, J.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: BELMONT PARK RACE 2 1 1/8M Inner turf CR: 101. Starters Allowance Purse 48000. INNER TURF (UP TO $8,640 NYSBFOA) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $16,000 OR LESS SINCE MARCH 1, 2013 AND SINCE THAT START HAVE NOT WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, OR STARTER. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; O lder, 123 lbs. Non-winners of two races at a mile or over since February 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). (Rail at 9 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SCREENPLAY broke alertly and maintained command, was rated towards the inside until the quarter pole, responded positively when given its cue, scampered away from the competition travelling through the furlong grounds, lost a good chunk of the advantage thereafter yet remained comfortably in the clear. NINEINTHENINE four wide and roused by the five-sixteenths pole, rallied for the place. DAYS RIDE took up the chase from the twp path, was along for the show. ABILIO three wide around both turns, was through after going three-quarters. SKIFFS BREWMEISTER three wide and under a full drive by the five-sixteenths marker, made no impact. ALE faltered off a ground-saving journey. SOUTHERN PROPER in the two path, prompted the winner for six furlong before giving way.

ENTRY.NAME: Screenplay
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated inside to 1/4,kicked away 1/4-1/8,comfortably in the clear

ENTRY.NAME: Days Ride
ENTRY.OWNER: Winning Move Stable and Klesaris Steve
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased near 2p, along for the show

ENTRY.NAME: Nineinthenine
ENTRY.COMMENT: off inside, 4w & driving by 5/16,rallied for place

ENTRY.NAME: Southern Proper
ENTRY.OWNER: Young Jay F and Nickel Dime Stable

RACE.RACE_TEXT: BELMONT PARK RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 74. Maiden Claiming Purse 51000. (UP TO $9,000 NYSBFOA) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $65,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BREACH OF DUTY chased the front runners while taking the two path for the majority of the way around the bend, tipped outward and challenged in earnest from the four path heading into the stretch, gained control by the end of the next furlong and drew off. GABBY'S BROWN stalked the pacesetter from the two path, was positioned between rivals from the five-sixteenths pole to upper stretch, proved no match for the winner while holding on well enough to secure second. MAY FLOWERS forwardly placed three wide, crept up towards the front runners after going more than halfway around the turn, got set down heading home, weakened belatedly. FERZETTI was placed over to the rail, made a sustained run to rally into prominence by midstre6tch, was forced to steady and alter course after closing in on traffic at the eighth pole, mustered up a mild response after finishing the move. CORAL BEACH saved ground and failed to menace. RIDDLE ME THIS raced along the outside and was outrun. DELIGHTFUL ERIN gained the lead shortly after the start, got guided over to the rail, faced off against a pair of rivals during the late stages of the run around the bend, had the winner arrive on the scene as the half was being completed, yielded to the pressure and backed away. CADILLAC ROSE commenced the stretch six wide, had little left and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Breach of Duty
ENTRY.COMMENT: chase trio turn,bid 4w into lane, drew off

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Pin Oak Stud, LLC & Mr. & Mrs. DanDayton

ENTRY.NAME: Riddle Me This
ENTRY.OWNER: Dubb, Michael, Bethlehem Stables and The Elkstone Group

ENTRY.NAME: Gabby's Brown
ENTRY.OWNER: Golden Goose Enterprise LLC Sunrise Stables and Sacks Lee

ENTRY.NAME: Delightful Erin
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied inside, faced off versus pair 6/16-upper,gave way

ENTRY.NAME: May Flowers
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w,outside pair on turn, weakened final furlong

RACE.RACE_TEXT: BELMONT PARK RACE 4 1 1/4M Inner turf CR: 105. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 80000. INNER TURF (UP TO $14,400 NYSBFOA) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $10,000 TWICE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $62,500. Three Y ear Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Other Than Claiming, Or Starter At A Mile Or Over Since February 1, 2014 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $62,500 (Allowance Horses Preferred)(Non-starters For A Claiming Price Of $25,000 Or Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred). (Rail at 9 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLEARBROOK attended the pace from just off the inside, came under urging at the five-sixteenths, angled three wide into upper stretch, rallied to seize command a sixteenth out and inched away late on to prevail. PREMIUM (GB) cut the pace along the inside in hand, got set down spinning just off the inside for home, dug in under challenge through the final furlong, got headed a sixteenth out, continued on willingly for the place. LITTLE JOURNEY (FR) coaxed at the start, settled just off the inside in mid pack, came under encouragement at the five-sixteenths, angled four wide into upper stretch, offered up a mild kick for the show. NEOLEXIA just off the inside towards the rear, came under a ride three furlongs out, cornered four to five wide into upper stretch, offered up a mild bid to garner the last major share. SABBATICAL tracked the pace along the inside in range, got spirited up at the five-sixteenths, cut the corner into upper stretch, made no headway. OASIS AT MIDNIGHT saved ground at the rear, grew detached from the main body of the field a half a mile from home, made no impact.

ENTRY.NAME: Oasis At Midnight
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved grd at rear, grew detached 1/2p, no impact

ENTRY.NAME: Premium (GB)
ENTRY.COMMENT: cut pace inside in hand, set down 2w 1/4, headed 1/16, willingly

ENTRY.NAME: Sabbatical
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked ins in range, asked 5/16, cut corner, no headway

ENTRY.NAME: Clearbrook
ENTRY.COMMENT: attended 2p, asked 5/16, 3w upper, up 1/16p, inched away

ENTRY.NAME: Neolexia
ENTRY.COMMENT: towards rear 2p, urged 3/8, 4-5w upper, mild bid

ENTRY.NAME: Little Journey (FR)
ENTRY.OWNER: Gramm, Marshall K., Laymon, Steve, Pitts, Gary and Pietrangelo, Michael A.
ENTRY.COMMENT: coaxed st, 2p mid pack, urged 5/16, 4w upper, mild kick

RACE.RACE_TEXT: BELMONT PARK RACE 5 6F Turf CR: 87. Claiming Purse 34000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners of a race since February 1 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Winners Preferred). (If the Stewards consider it in advisable to run this race on the turf course, this race will be run at Six Furlongs on the main track.) (Rail at 27 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AMBER MORNING along the inside for most of the way down the backstretch, chose the two path as the way to go around the turn, sat reserved for nearly a half, picked up ground readily when set down for the drive, wrested the advantage with under a sixteenth to go, then dug in to preserve it. ROCK N COZY strung out four wide midway on the turn, swung one path wider into the stretch, came home willingly but had to settle for the place. VERONICA BAY three wide on the turn, had a good finish down the outside of the course to rally for the show award. LAKEVIEW LADY made contact with CALM REPLY at the start, accompanied the leader from the two path for a half, closed in from upper to midstretch, flattened out. BENNY'S BULLET broke alertly and maintained the advantage, made it over to rail before reaching the end of the backstretch, felt an uptick in pressure heading for the quarter pole and was let out in response to it, offered resistance before releasing the lead with less than a sixteenth remaining. BOCA BABE three wide and asked by the three-eighths pole, tired. OVER MY HEAD nestled between rivals for a good portion of the way on the turn, had no rally. CALM REPLY bumped at the start, was placed along the rail nearing the end of the backstretch, rode it for next quarter, commenced the stretch four wide, had no response. UTOPIAN WIFE raced three wide on the turn and was outrun. PENELLA faded off a ground-saving journey.

ENTRY.NAME: Over My Head
ENTRY.COMMENT: neslted btwn foes, urged heading home, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Calm Reply
ENTRY.COMMENT: bump start, rode rail turn, 4w uper,no impact

ENTRY.NAME: Benny's Bullet
ENTRY.OWNER: Canzone, Sr., Peter J. and Eloise
ENTRY.COMMENT: rate inside for half, relinquished final 70 yards

RACE.RACE_TEXT: BELMONT PARK RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 84. Maiden Special Weight Purse 60000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY. Weight, 120 lbs. (Non-starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: REGAL MINISTER dueled from just off the inside with SAINT JOSEPH to his inside, got let out three wide into upper stretch, dug in under challenge from a trio, held on determined to repel those foes and prevail on the wire. GOT WINGED tracked the pace along the inside, shifted three wide put to encouragement at the five-sixteenths, angled four wide for home, rallied to threaten through the final eighth but could offer no extra and was forced to settle for the place. BUDDY THE ELF three to four wide in range of the duel up front, got set down five wide into upper stretch, offered up a mild kick to challenge through the final furlong but was outfinished by the top pair. SAINT JOSEPH dueled inside of REGAL MINISTER, got let out at the head of the stretch just off the inside, fought on inside through the length of the stretch but was out kicked to the wire. CATS LANDING four to five wide in pursuit from mid pack, came under urging at the five-sixteenths, continued five wide for home, made no late headway. MR HARLAN saved ground in pursuit from mid pack under urging from three furlongs out and weakened in the stretch. GOLDEN LUCK broke in under hustling at the start bumping COPERNICUS, chased three wide from towards the rear pushed along, angled six wide into upper stretch, made no impact. SUPER PSYCHE three wide towards the rear, came under urging midway on the turn, angled seven wide at the quarter pole, offered no response. B. B.'S REMINGTON three wide in pursuit from mid pack, came under a ride at the three-eighths, angled four wide into upper stretch, made no impact. COPERNICUS bumped on both sides at the start by rivals breaking his way, chased four to five wide through the turn, angled five to six wide into upper stretch, tired. DIVINE GLORY broke out at the start bumping COPERNICUS, saved ground towards the rear, came under urging three furlongs out, spun three wide for home, made no impact. THIRTY PERCENT broke in at the start, chased three wide from towards the rear, grew detached into upper stretch, was not persevered with, pulled up in the final seventy yard and subsequently walked off.

ENTRY.NAME: Thirty Percent
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in st, chased 3w at rear, eased str, pulled up, walked off

ENTRY.NAME: Mr Harlan
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved grd mid pack, urged 3/8, weakened

ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled ins, let out 1/4p, 3w upper, fought on, out kicked

ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled 2p, asked 3w 1/4p, dug in determined, repelled trio

ENTRY.NAME: Got Winged
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked ins, angled 3w 5/16, 4w upper, dug in, no extra

ENTRY.NAME: Buddy the Elf
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3-4w in range, asked 5w upper, mild kick, outfinished

ENTRY.NAME: Divine Glory
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out st, saved grd towards rear, 3w upper, no impact

ENTRY.NAME: Copernicus
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped both sides st, chased 4-5w, 5-6w upper, tired

ENTRY.NAME: Golden Luck
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in hustled st, 3w towards rear, 6w upper, no impact

ENTRY.NAME: Cats Landing
ENTRY.OWNER: Caterbone, James F. and Caterbone, Margaret
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4-5w mid pack, urged 5/16, 5w upper, no headway

ENTRY.NAME: Super Psyche
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w towards rear, urged 3/8, 7w upper, no response

RACE.RACE_TEXT: BELMONT PARK RACE 7 1 1/16M Inner turf CR: 101. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 65000. INNER TURF FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $13,000 TWICE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE O F $40,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners of two races other than Claiming, or Starter at a mile or over since February 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000 (Allowance Horses Preferred)(Non- starters For A Claiming Price Of $25,000 Or Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred). (Rail at 9 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOBRIDGE sat reserved in midpack in the two path for the opening three-quarters, angled into the five path during the initial portion of the stretch drive, closed in readily and took over by the end of the furlong grounds, kicked away. JONRAH made contact with HALF WILDCAT as they departed the first turn, raced forwardly placed in the three path, showed some courage procuring the place. STATUS OF FORCES rated stalking the pace from the two path, lacked the needed late response. ANALYSIS slipped off the inside route as three-quarters was being completed, had a good kick down the center of the course to grab the last major check. MORNING CALM strung out three wide on the clubhouse turn, rallied mildly to improve position. HALF WILDCAT bumped with JONRAH entering the backstretch, was unhurried mainly from the two path to the quarter pole, made no impact. MAJESTIC RAFFY saved ground to the quarter pole, made no headway after getting angled outward. SNEAKY KITTEN rated in the pocket for over six furlongs, gained entrance into the stretch from the two path, checked when stuck behind rivals shortly afterwards, tipped towards the middle of the course, had enough clearance to launch a rally, but didn't. ELROI saved ground to the quarter pole, had no rally. GOSSIP COLUMN raced along the outside and was outrun. ALARMED NDANGEROUS off the inside and put to a prolonged drive, tired. BREATHAWAY rated along the inside, succumbed when challenged.

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Oak Bluff Stables LLC & Christophe Clement

ENTRY.NAME: Sneaky Kitten
ENTRY.OWNER: Ramsey, Kenneth L. and Sarah K.
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pocket to 1/4,steadied in traffic upper, clear, empty

ENTRY.NAME: Jonrah
ENTRY.OWNER: Winning Move Stable and Team Classic Racing
ENTRY.COMMENT: bump early,forwardly placed 3 wide,good courage for place

RACE.RACE_TEXT: BELMONT PARK RACE 8 1M Dirt CR: 101. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 80000. (UP TO $14,400 NYSBFOA) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $10,000 TWICE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $62,500. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Other Than Claiming, Or Starter At A Mile Or Over Since February 1, 2014 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $62,500 (Allowance Horses Preferred)(Non-starters For A Claiming Price Of $25,000 O r Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BAY OF PLENTY established the front just off the inside in hand, remained patiently handled attended to the outside through the turn, spun just off the inside for home, got asked at the three-sixteenths, edged away under a light drive before being geared down in the late stages. MOSLER well off the inside early on forwardly placed, shifted to the three path at the half mile pole, attended the pace two to three wide through the turn, got set down at the quarter pole, proved no match for the top one while cutting into the margin in the late stages of the geared down foe with a mild kick. VINCEREMOS three wide in pursuit, came under encouragement at the five-sixteenths, continued two to three wide for home, kept on through the stretch for the show honors. CRUSHING just off the inside in pursuit, got put to encouragement at the five-sixteenths, cornered just off the inside into upper stretch, made no headway. SAINT VIGEUR saved ground near the rear, came under urging three furlongs out and angled out two paths to circled the retreating BETWEENHEREANDCOOL at the five-sixteenths, shifted back inside to cut the corner into upper stretch and offered no response. BETWEENHEREANDCOOL tracked the pace along the inside in range, retreated through the latter portion of the turn, tired and was eased in the stretch then walked off after the finish.

ENTRY.NAME: Bay of Plenty
ENTRY.COMMENT: in hand 2p, asked 3/16, edged away, geared down late

ENTRY.NAME: Betweenhereandcool
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked ins in range, retreated latter turn, tired, eased

ENTRY.NAME: Vinceremos
ENTRY.OWNER: WinStar Farm LLC and Twin Creeks Racing Stables, LLC

ENTRY.NAME: Mosler
ENTRY.COMMENT: well off inside, attended 2-3w turn, asked 1/4p, mild kick

ENTRY.NAME: Saint Vigeur
ENTRY.OWNER: Warren, Jr., Mr. and Mrs. William K.
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved grd near rear, urged 3/8, cut corner, no response

RACE.RACE_TEXT: BELMONT PARK RACE 9 6F Turf CR: 74. Maiden Claiming Purse 41000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000 (Non-starters For A Claiming Price Of $16,000 Or Less I n The Last Start Preferred). (If the Stewards consider it inadvisable to run this race on the turf course, this race will be run at Six Furlongs on the main track.) (Rail at 27 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LAURA CAN DISCO ducked outward slightly right after the start, moved up to assume a forward position, stalked the pace from the two path, moved outward and issued a challenge three wide heading home, took over and scampered away from the others, left the eighth pole holding its biggest advantage, dug in well enough in the late stages to arrive at the finish line first. MAURA'S PASS settled into midpack after the start, had the pilot take hold when momentarily wedged in between rivals past midpoint on the turn, was forced to be kept on hold lacking sufficient racing room nearing the quarter pole, remained stuck in traffic during the initial portion of the stretch drive, altered course towards the middle of the course, kicked into her best stride after ending the maneuver and rallied for the place. LLOYD HARBOR tracked the front runners from the pocket, continued onward well enough down the stretch to take the show award. SENSO stumbled at the start, underwent a four wide pursuit on the turn, flattened out and had to settle for the last major check. UNREPENTED four wide at the three-eighths pole, rallied mildly to mainly improve position. MARY'S IN UTOPIA off the inside, was driven four wide into the stretch, got taken hold when momentarily caught in some traffic in upper stretch, lacked the needed late response. YOU TAKE THE CAKE was pushed out for a couple of jumps by an errant EAST COAST EXPRESS, went on to save ground on the turn to no avail. COUNTESS TWICE in the four path at the five-sixteenths marker, failed to menace. QUIT SMOKIN rated in the two path for a half, took over coming to the quarter pole, yielded before completing the next furlong and backed away. NO TRESPASSERS slipped off the inside route past the five-sixteenths pole, came up empty. EAST COAST EXPRESS broke to the outside, was pulled away from the nearest opponent but not before some light contact between them, showed the way from the inside, offered no resistance getting displaced as the half was being finished and faltered. LOVELY LANIE three wide at the five-sixteenths pole, showed only brief foot.

ENTRY.NAME: You Take the Cake
ENTRY.COMMENT: push out bit start,saved ground on turn, no factor

ENTRY.NAME: Mary's in Utopia
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2p,angle 4w into lane, brief traffic upper, no late response

ENTRY.NAME: Senso
ENTRY.COMMENT: stumbled start,4w pursuit on turn, flattened out

ENTRY.NAME: Unrepented
ENTRY.OWNER: Iglesias, Jesse, Imperio, Michael and Blue Crown Stable

ENTRY.NAME: Laura Can Disco
ENTRY.COMMENT: duck out after st,2pto 5/16,bid 3w into lane, held well enough
